    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Lavandula angustifolia are its antimicrobial effects, which are attributed to the bioactive compounds, including volatile oils such as linalool and linalyl acetate, that inhibit the growth of bacteria and fungi. The antioxidant properties of the plant are due to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids, which scavenge free radicals and protect against oxidative stress. This plant also exhibits anti-inflammatory effects, with saponins and terpenoids contributing to its ability to reduce inflammation and alleviate pain. Furthermore, Lavandula angustifolia possesses anxiolytic properties, which are partly due to the sedative effects of its volatile oils, that help to reduce anxiety and promote relaxation. The sedative properties of the plant are also a result of its bioactive compounds, such as flavonoids and terpenoids, that interact with the GABA receptor and promote a calming effect.",
