    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Lavandula angustifolia are linalool, linalyl acetate, camphor, borneol, and caryophyllene oxide. Linalool, a sesquiterpene alcohol, is known for its anxiolytic and sedative properties, reducing anxiety and promoting relaxation. Linalyl acetate, a monoterpenic ester, has antimicrobial and antiseptic properties, making it effective against bacteria, viruses, and fungi. Camphor, a monoterpenic ketone, is used for its analgesic and antiseptic properties, relieving pain and inflammation. Caryophyllene oxide, a sesquiterpene epoxide, exhibits anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties, reducing inflammation and oxidative stress in the body.",
