    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Lavandula angustifolia are derived from its flowers and leaves, which are rich in bioactive compounds such as linalool and linalyl acetate. Lavender oil, obtained through steam distillation, is widely used for its calming and sedative properties, and is often used in aromatherapy to reduce anxiety and promote relaxation. Lavender tea, a herbal infusion, can be prepared by steeping dried flowers in hot water, and is traditionally used to promote a good night's sleep and alleviate digestive issues. Lavender salve, a topical preparation, is often used to soothe skin irritations, wounds, and burns due to its anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties. Additionally, lavender tincture and infusion are also used to support mental health and well-being, with the former often used as a medicinal extract and the latter as a calming and sleep-promoting beverage.",
